sect1.para:
The Hmong in Laos were preliterate farmers with generally limited or no access to education. They lived in very primitive and traditional circumstances and had no access to the modern world or modern medicine. When immigrating to the US, many Hmong experienced culture shock in a world that was completely unfamiliar to them. Depression, post-traumatic stress disorder, and suicide are prevalent in this population. More recent immigrants have received some education and have been exposed to the modern world. This aggregate profile may not fit well-acculturated Hmong individuals in the US based on length of time in the US and the diverse characteristics of culture (see Chap. 

                  1

            ).
